          }
        },
        "text_G8tYQm": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To take a full and rejuvenating breath, ensure your posture is straight, and your shoulders are relaxed. Inhale deeply through your nose, allowing your diaphragm (a thin, dome-shaped muscle that sits below your lungs and heart) to expand fully. Exhale slowly and completely.</p><p>The breath should not be forced, without tension in your body, and without a loud sound.</p><p>James Nestor, the famous researcher on breathing, mentions that a rhythm of “5.5-second inhales followed by 5.5-second exhales” is the most efficient breathing pattern.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
